  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7034.45 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are currently in a neutral hedging posture but likely starting to sell delta as spot approaches the 7050 resistance wall. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls stacked above (7050, 7100) creates a strong ceiling effect where dealer selling pressure intensifies on any move higher. Key level to watch is the 7050 strike with 11.6B in positive gamma - a break above triggers heavy dealer selling while a rejection confirms the wall's strength and supports mean reversion back toward 7015-7000.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong resistance at 7050 with downward pressure if SPX tries to push higher.",
